Tests failed — the `categorizeGrammarError` function has a greedy article match. Let me have the coder fix this.

I can see the problem clearly. The article rule's patterns `/\bthe\b/` and `/\b(a|an)\b/` match common English words "the", "a", "an" appearing in nearly every sentence. Since article is checked first, it greedily matches almost everything.

The fix: remove those overly broad patterns and keep only `/\barticles?\b/` and `/\bdeterminer\b/` which match the grammar concept terms. The ordering can stay the same since the priority test (line 141) expects article before tense.

