  "description": "All current practice cards are siloed by module (speaking, listening, grammar, vocabulary, writing). Research on interleaved practice shows mixing skill types in one session significantly improves retention. Add a 'Quick Mixed Review' card to the Home page that runs a rapid-fire 10-question review pulling items from multiple modules: (1) 3-4 vocabulary words due for review from vocabulary_progress WHERE next_review_at <= now — show word, pick correct meaning from 4 options; (2) 3-4 grammar corrections from messages.feedback_json WHERE is_correct = false — show original sentence, user picks the corrected version from 2 options; (3) 2-3 pronunciation items from pronunciation_attempts with low scores — show the phrase, user reads it aloud and gets quick pass/fail. Items are shuffled randomly. At the end, show a summary with per-module breakdown and overall score.\n\nBackend: Add new endpoint GET /api/dashboard/mixed-review?count=10 in app/routers/dashboard.py. Add DAL function get_mixed_review_items() in app/dal/dashboard.py that queries vocabulary_progress (due words with meanings/wrong options), messages (recent grammar errors with corrections), and pronunciation_attempts (low-scoring phrases). Return a shuffled array of {type: 'vocab'|'grammar'|'pronunciation', ...item-specific fields}.\n\nFrontend: Create new QuickMixedReviewCard.tsx component with phases: idle → drilling (show items one-by-one with type-appropriate UI) → results. Add it prominently on the Home page above or alongside the QuickPracticeHub. Wire up new API function getMixedReviewItems() in api.ts. Vocabulary items use button selection, grammar items use button selection, pronunciation items use the existing useSpeechRecognition hook + api.checkPronunciation for quick evaluation.\n\nNo schema changes needed — all data comes from existing tables.",
