{
  "type": "bugfix",
  "title": "Fix coerce_bool(None) inflating grammar accuracy for null is_correct",
  "description": "Three grammar accuracy functions in `app/dal/conversation.py` mishandle feedback where `is_correct` is stored as JSON `null` (Python `None`). The root cause: `coerce_bool(None)` returns `True` (its default parameter), so messages with null `is_correct` are counted as grammatically correct.\n\n1. `get_conversation_metrics` (line 812-815): When `is_correct` is None, the key IS in the dict so the `'is_correct' not in feedback` guard passes. Then `coerce_bool(None)` returns True, inflating the per-conversation grammar accuracy shown in conversation summaries. Fix: add `or feedback['is_correct'] is None` to the skip condition.\n\n2. `get_grammar_accuracy` (line 424-426): Missing the `'is_correct' in feedback` guard entirely — every parsed feedback dict is counted in `total_checked` even without `is_correct`, deflating accuracy. Plus the same `coerce_bool(None)=True` bug when `is_correct` is null. Fix: add an `is_correct is None` skip guard matching the pattern in `get_conversation_metrics`.\n\n3. `get_random_grammar_mistake` (line 1144): `coerce_bool(None)` returns True, causing messages with null `is_correct` to be silently skipped as 'correct', hiding potential mistakes from the daily drill picker. Fix: add explicit None check before coerce_bool.\n\nNote: `_normalize_grammar_feedback` in the router ensures NEW feedback always has a proper boolean `is_correct`. But feedback stored before this normalization was added (or from any bypass path) can have null values, making this a real data integrity issue.\n\nThe existing test `test_missing_is_correct_not_counted` (line 655) asserts `total_checked==1` for feedback without `is_correct` — this should be updated to `total_checked==0` to match the corrected behavior (consistent with `get_conversation_metrics` which already skips such messages).",
  "files_to_modify": ["app/dal/conversation.py", "tests/unit/test_conversation_dal.py"],
  "priority": "high",
  "estimated_complexity": "small"
}
